#: static/build.html:379
msgid ""
"For various reasons, there are a number of prebuilt components in the OS "
"source tree. The majority of them are only used in the development process "
"and are not included in the OS. For the prebuilts that are included, they "
"are usually either an unavoidable dependency or extremely complex to build "
"and not designed to be built as part of the OS build system. Many are "
"included simply for bootstrapping to avoid building the toolchain or to run "
"the build on a platform not supported by building the toolchain from source "
"(i.e. building on macOS). Others are legacy prebuilts from AOSP which are "
"being phased out and replaced with source code."
msgstr ""

#: static/build.html:383
msgid ""
"The kernel sources are built as part of the OS build system and produce "
"kernel binaries. However, these are still treated as prebuilts for the final"
" OS packaging steps. For generic targets (emulator, cuttlefish, hikey, "
"hikey960, etc.) and legacy non-GKI devices, the kernel modules are also "
"built and packaged. For GKI devices, the kernel modules are built from the "
"kernel source tree."
msgstr ""

#: static/build.html:387
msgid ""
"The emulator uses a kernel built from the Goldfish kernel tree. The kernel "
"binaries are built as part of the OS build and are treated as prebuilts in "
"the same way as other devices. The kernel is built as a separate step and "
"then copied to the prebuilts directory."
msgstr ""

#: static/build.html:392
msgid ""
"Microdroid uses a kernel built from the Goldfish kernel tree. The kernel "
"binaries are built as part of the OS build and are treated as prebuilts in "
"the same way as other devices."
msgstr ""

#: static/build.html:397
msgid ""
"The kernels for the 6th through 9th generation Pixels (Pixel 6 through Pixel"
" 9) are built from source and are not prebuilt. The kernel modules are built"
" from the kernel source tree as part of the OS build."
msgstr ""

#: static/build.html:402
msgid ""
"The kernels for the 10th generation Pixels (Pixel 10, Pixel 10 Pro, Pixel 10"
" Pro XL, Pixel 10 Pro Fold) are built from source and are not prebuilt. The "
"kernel modules are built from the kernel source tree as part of the OS "
"build."
msgstr ""

#: static/build.html:408
msgid ""
"Vanadium, the hardened Chromium browser and WebView, is included as a "
"prebuilt for the OS build. This is due to the complexity of building "
"Chromium as part of the OS build system. The source code for Vanadium is "
"available and it can be built separately, but it is not built as part of the"
" OS build process. The prebuilt is taken from the official Vanadium "
"releases."
msgstr ""

#: static/build.html:413
