#: static/camera-privacy-policy.html:6
msgid "Camera privacy policy | GrapheneOS"
msgstr ""

#: static/camera-privacy-policy.html:36
msgid "Camera privacy policy"
msgstr ""

#: static/camera-privacy-policy.html:37
msgid ""
"This app requires the Camera permission for the core functionality of the app. The\n"
"            Microphone permission is optional and only requested when starting video recording\n"
"            without disabling \"Include Audio\". Video can be recorded without granting Microphone\n"
"            access as long as \"Include Audio\" is disabled. Geotagging is disabled by default and\n"
"            enabling it will request the Location permission. The app doesn't require access to\n"
"            your media or other files. It stores files to the profile's Media Store and requests\n"
"            that they be placed in DCIM/Camera which doesn't require a permission. You can also\n"
"            choose to change the directory which will have you choose a directory for it to use\n"
"            via the system file manager."
msgstr ""

#: static/camera-privacy-policy.html:46
msgid ""
"This app implements the system camera intent interfaces enabling other apps to use\n"
"            it to take pictures or record videos with explicit user consent. Only the resulting\n"
"            image or video explicitly captured by the user is given to the app. On Android 11 and\n"
"            later, only a system camera app can provide the system camera intents. This app is the\n"
"            system camera app on GrapheneOS where it provides that functionality. The handling of\n"
"            the intents is carefully designed to make it harder to trick users into accidentally\n"
"            capturing an image by implementing a delay."
msgstr ""

#: static/camera-privacy-policy.html:53
msgid ""
"This app does not make any network connections and doesn't use any services. The\n"
"            app will never include any analytics/telemetry or any form of data collection. No\n"
"            connections will ever be made to a service without the user requesting it. It stores\n"
"            settings internally and pictures/videos captured by the user in Android's media store\n"
"            for the profile."
msgstr ""

#: static/camera-privacy-policy.html:58
msgid ""
"Unlike nearly any other QR/barcode scanning apps, QR/barcode scanning does not open\n"
"            the resulting URL automatically."
msgstr ""

