#: static/features.html:40
msgid ""
"GrapheneOS is a private and secure mobile operating system with great functionality\n"
"            and usability. It starts from the strong baseline of the\n"
"            "
msgstr ""

#: static/features.html:42
msgid "Android Open Source Project (AOSP)"
msgstr ""

#: static/features.html:42
msgid ""
" and\n"
"            takes great care to avoid increasing attack surface or hurting the strong security\n"
"            model. GrapheneOS makes substantial improvements to both privacy and security through\n"
"            many carefully designed features built to function against real adversaries. The\n"
"            project cares a lot about usability and app compatibility so those are taken into\n"
"            account for all of our features."
msgstr ""

#: static/features.html:48
msgid ""
"GrapheneOS is focused on substance rather than branding and marketing. It doesn't\n"
"            take the typical approach of piling on a bunch of insecure features depending on the\n"
"            adversaries not knowing about them and regressing actual privacy/security. It's a very\n"
"            technical project building privacy and security into the OS rather than including\n"
"            assorted unhelpful frills or bundling subjective third party apps choices."
msgstr ""

#: static/features.html:53
msgid ""
"GrapheneOS is also hard at work on filling in gaps from not bundling Google apps\n"
"            and services into the OS. We aren't against users using Google services but it doesn't\n"
"            belong integrated into the OS in an invasive way. GrapheneOS won't take the shortcut\n"
"            of simply bundling a very incomplete and poorly secured third party reimplementation\n"
"            of Google services into the OS. That wouldn't ever be something users could rely upon.\n"
"            It will also always be chasing a moving target while offering poorer security than the\n"
"            real thing if the focus is on simply getting things working without great care for\n"
"            doing it robustly and securely."
msgstr ""

#: static/features.html:61
msgid ""
"This page provides an overview of currently implemented features differentiating\n"
"            GrapheneOS from AOSP. It doesn't document our many historical features that are no\n"
"            longer included for one reason or another. Many of our features were implemented in\n"
"            AOSP, Linux, "
