#: static/releases.html:500
msgid ""
"These releases are available as both tags in the source code repositories and\n"
"                official builds."
msgstr ""

#: static/releases.html:502
msgid ""
"The factory images are used for the initial installation and can be verified with\n"
"                OpenSSH. See the "
msgstr ""

#: static/releases.html:503
msgid "installation page"
msgstr ""

#: static/releases.html:503
msgid " for details."
msgstr ""

#: static/releases.html:504
msgid ""
"GrapheneOS uses automatic over-the-air updates, but full update packages are listed\n"
"                below for uncommon use cases like never connecting the device to the internet. A full\n"
"                update package can upgrade from any past version to the new version. The over-the-air\n"
"                updates use delta update packages when available. Those aren't currently linked below\n"
"                but may be in the future once they're being used more consistently. Update packages\n"
"                are not for performing the initial installation and you should ignore incorrect guides\n"
"                trying to use them to install the OS."
msgstr ""

#: static/releases.html:511
msgid ""
"The update packages have an internal signature verified by the update client (or\n"
"                recovery when sideloading). Downgrade attacks are also prevented, and downgrades\n"
"                cannot be done unless a special downgrade update package has been signed with the\n"
"                release key. The internal payload for "
msgstr ""

#: static/releases.html:514
msgid ""
" is also signed,\n"
"                providing another layer of signature verification and downgrade protection. Verified\n"
"                boot and the hardware-backed keystore also act as a final layer of protection."
msgstr ""

#: static/releases.html:517
msgid ""
"Releases are tested by the developers and are then pushed out via the Alpha\n"
"                channel. The release is then pushed out via the Beta channel shortly afterwards.\n"
"                Finally, the release is then pushed out via the Stable channel after being tested\n"
"                by users using the Beta channel. In some cases, problems are caught during Beta\n"
"                channel testing and a new release is made via the Beta channel to replace the\n"
"                aborted one. In general, it's not possible to downgrade unless a downgrade update\n"
"                package is generated, so use the Stable channel if you cannot tolerate dealing with\n"
"                temporary issues while a new release for the Beta channel is being created."
msgstr ""

#: static/releases.html:528
msgid "Releases are announced on this page and included in an "
msgstr ""

#: static/releases.html:528 static/releases.html:614
msgid "atom feed"
msgstr ""

#: static/releases.html:528
msgid ""
" usable from any standard\n"
"                feed reader app. A release announcement indicates that the\n"
"                source code tags are available and that the official builds\n"
"                will soon be pushed out via the Alpha channel."
msgstr ""

