msgstr ""

#: static/usage.html:382
msgid ""
"The \"Check for updates\" option will manually trigger an update check as soon as\n"
"                    possible. It will still wait for the configuration conditions listed below to be\n"
"                    satisfied, such as being connected to the internet via one of the permitted network\n"
"                    types."
msgstr ""

#: static/usage.html:386
msgid ""
"The \"Release channel\" setting can be changed from the default Stable channel to the\n"
"                    Beta channel if you want to help with testing. The Beta channel will usually simply\n"
"                    follow the Stable channel, but the Beta channel may be used to experiment with new\n"
"                    features."
msgstr ""

#: static/usage.html:390
msgid ""
"The \"Permitted networks\" setting controls which networks will be used to perform\n"
"                    updates. It defaults to using any network connection. It can be set to \"Non-roaming\"\n"
"                    to disable it when the cellular service is marked as roaming or \"Unmetered\" to disable\n"
"                    it on cellular networks and also Wi-Fi networks marked as metered."
msgstr ""

#: static/usage.html:394
#, python-format
msgid ""
"The \"Require battery above warning level\" setting controls whether updates will\n"
"                    only be performed when the battery is above the level where the warning message is\n"
"                    shown. The standard value is at 15% capacity."
msgstr ""

#: static/usage.html:397
msgid ""
"The \"Require device to be charging\" setting controls whether updates will\n"
"                    only be performed when the device is charging."
msgstr ""

#: static/usage.html:399
msgid ""
"Enabling the opt-in \"Automatic reboot\" setting allows the updater to reboot the\n"
"                    device after an update once it has been idle for a long time. When this setting is\n"
"                    enabled, a device can take care of any number of updates completely automatically even\n"
"                    if it's left completely idle."
msgstr ""

#: static/usage.html:403
msgid ""
"The \"Notification settings\" option is a shortcut to the System Updater notification\n"
"                    settings which allows you to control notification settings from System Updater such as\n"
"                    notification dot, lock screen, and noisy or silent notifications. These notifications\n"
"                    include updater errors, progress, already up to date, and reboot prompts. By default all\n"
"                    notifications are enabled."
msgstr ""

#: static/usage.html:411
msgid ""
"The update server isn't a trusted party since updates are signed and verified along\n"
"                    with downgrade attacks being prevented. The update protocol doesn't send identifiable\n"
"                    information to the update server and works well over a VPN or Tor. GrapheneOS isn't\n"
"                    able to comply with a government order to build, sign and ship a malicious update to a\n"
"                    specific user's device based on information like the IMEI, serial number, etc. The\n"
"                    update server only ends up knowing the IP address used to connect to it and the\n"
"                    version being upgraded from based on the requested incremental."
msgstr ""

#: static/usage.html:418
msgid ""
"Android updates can support serialno constraints to make them validate only on a\n"
"                    certain device but GrapheneOS rejects any update with a serialno constraint for both\n"
"                    over-the-air updates (Updater app) and sideloaded updates (recovery)."
msgstr ""

#: static/usage.html:424
msgid ""
"It's highly recommended to leave automatic updates enabled and to configure\n"
"                    the permitted networks if the bandwidth usage is a problem on your mobile data\n"
"                    connection. However, it's possible to turn off the update client by going to\n"
"                    "
msgstr ""

