#: static/usage.html:964
msgid ""
"\n"
"                        which are disabled by default and control whether apps with the required permissions\n"
"                        can scan when Wi-Fi and Bluetooth are otherwise disabled."
msgstr ""

#: static/usage.html:968
msgid ""
"Re-routing location to the OS geolocation service will use more power than\n"
"                    using the Google Play geolocation service unless you enable our opt-in\n"
"                    "
msgstr ""

#: static/usage.html:971
msgid ""
"The Google Location Accuracy and Google settings activities would normally\n"
"                    be integrated into the OS but we don't include any of the standard Google Play\n"
"                    integration so there needs to be an app providing a way to access them."
msgstr ""

#: static/usage.html:974
msgid ""
"The menu also provides links to this usage guide, Play services system\n"
"                    settings, Play Store system settings and Google settings. The Play services and\n"
"                    Play Store system settings are only included for convenience since they can be\n"
"                    accessed the same way as any other app via "
msgstr ""

#: static/usage.html:981
msgid ""
"Location sharing in Google Maps is implemented in Google Play services. It\n"
"                    requires enabling both the Location permission with \"Allow all the time\" and the\n"
"                    Physical activity permission for Google Play services. Our location rerouting\n"
"                    feature reimplementing the Google Play location service using the OS location\n"
"                    service does not apply to Google Play services itself, so Google Play services\n"
"                    won't use the OS network location service. You can use the instructions above\n"
"                    for enabling network location via Google Play if you want this. You could\n"
"                    continue using rerouting for other apps or disable it to avoid needing 2\n"
"                    separate network location services enabled."
msgstr ""

#: static/usage.html:993
msgid ""
"Our compatibility layer has to be expanded on a case-by-case basis to teach\n"
"                    Play services to work as a regular app without any of the invasive access and\n"
"                    integration it expects. In many cases, it doesn't truly need the access or we\n"
"                    can teach it to use the regular approach available to a normal app. In some\n"
"                    cases, the functionality it offers fundamentally requires privileged access\n"
"                    and cannot be supported. For example, Android Auto cannot be supported by\n"
"                    default as part of the baseline compatibility layer, but is supported as an\n"
"                    extension of it with dedicated toggles for the functionality that's not\n"
"                    possible to implement another way. The same applies to other highly invasive\n"
"                    OS integration/control or privileged access to hardware. Our compatibility\n"
"                    layer is a very actively developed work in progress and most of the remaining\n"
"                    unavailable functionality is quickly becoming supported. In the future, we can\n"
"                    also support redirection for more APIs such as FIDO2 rather than only the\n"
"                    geolocation service."
msgstr ""

#: static/usage.html:1007
msgid ""
"Functionality depending on the OS integrating Play services and using it as\n"
"                    a backend is unavailable. An OS integrating Play uses it as the backend for OS\n"
"                    services such as geolocation. GrapheneOS never uses it as the backend/provider\n"
"                    for OS services. In cases such as text-to-speech (TTS) where the OS allows the\n"
"                    user to choose the provider, Play services can often be used. It's on a level\n"
"                    playing field with other apps on GrapheneOS."
msgstr ""

#: static/usage.html:1017
msgid ""
