msgstr ""

#: static/articles/sitewide-advertising-industry-opt-out.html:37
msgid ""
"\n"
"            provides a way to list the authorized sellers of ads for a domain. The\n"
"            "
msgstr ""

#: static/articles/sitewide-advertising-industry-opt-out.html:39
msgid "app-ads.txt specification"
msgstr ""

#: static/articles/sitewide-advertising-industry-opt-out.html:39
msgid ""
"\n"
"            extends this to cover apps tied to the domain. As a domain owner, this is a valuable\n"
"            way to crack down on fraudulent usage of your domain including by adware."
msgstr ""

#: static/articles/sitewide-advertising-industry-opt-out.html:42
msgid ""
"For domains without any third party advertising including those without any ads at\n"
"            all, you should serve both "
msgstr ""

#: static/articles/sitewide-advertising-industry-opt-out.html:43
msgid ""
" from a\n"
"            web server with the placeholder record defined by the specification:"
msgstr ""

#: static/articles/sitewide-advertising-industry-opt-out.html:46
msgid ""
"The placeholder record formally disallows buying and selling ads on behalf of the\n"
"            domain including for any subdomains. This prevents fraudulently buying and selling ads\n"
"            for your domain anywhere that ads.txt and app-ads.txt are enforced."
msgstr ""

#: static/articles/sitewide-advertising-industry-opt-out.html:49
msgid ""
"It's in the interest of most ad tech companies to enforce these standards due to\n"
"            losses from ad fraud so adoption is increasingly widespread."
msgstr ""

#: static/articles/sitewide-advertising-industry-opt-out.html:51
msgid ""
"Browser extension malware injecting ads into sites is very common and this is a way\n"
"            for sites to hurt those malware developers where it hurts: their pocketbook."
msgstr ""

#: static/articles/sitewide-advertising-industry-opt-out.html:53
msgid ""
"These standards have a limited scope and were primarily created to address the cost\n"
"            of ad fraud for the advertising industry, but they do offer value for domain owners to\n"
"            protect their reputation and discourage adware."
msgstr ""

#: static/history/copperheados.html:6
msgid "CopperheadOS | History | GrapheneOS"
