"                    interface will boot the OS."
msgstr ""

#: static/install/cli.html:408 static/install/web.html:321
msgid ""
"During first setup, the final screen will contain a toggle regarding OEM\n"
"                    unlocking which is checked by default. This will disable OEM unlocking, which is\n"
"                    recommended."
msgstr ""

#: static/install/cli.html:411 static/install/web.html:324
msgid ""
"If you need to enable or disable OEM unlocking in the future, it can be done\n"
"                    in the developer settings menu within the operating system."
msgstr ""

#: static/install/cli.html:416 static/install/web.html:329
msgid ""
"The verified boot and attestation features provided by the supported\n"
"                    devices can be used to verify that the hardware, firmware and GrapheneOS\n"
"                    installation are genuine. Even if the computer you used to flash GrapheneOS\n"
"                    was compromised and an attacker replaced GrapheneOS with their own malicious\n"
"                    OS, it can be detected with these features."
msgstr ""

#: static/install/cli.html:421 static/install/web.html:334
msgid ""
"Verified boot verifies the entirety of the firmware and OS images on every\n"
"                    boot. The public key for the firmware images is burned into fuses in the SoC at\n"
"                    the factory. Firmware security updates also update the rollback index burned\n"
"                    into fuses to provide rollback protection."
msgstr ""

#: static/install/cli.html:425 static/install/web.html:338
msgid ""
"The final firmware boot stage before the OS is responsible for verifying\n"
"                    it. For the stock OS, it uses a hard-wired public key. Installing GrapheneOS\n"
"                    flashes the GrapheneOS verified boot public key to the secure element. Each\n"
"                    boot, this key is loaded and used to verify the OS. For both the stock OS and\n"
"                    GrapheneOS, a rollback index based on the security patch level is loaded from\n"
"                    the secure element to provide rollback protection."
msgstr ""

#: static/install/cli.html:436 static/install/web.html:349
msgid ""
"GrapheneOS provides our Auditor app for using a combination of the\n"
"                        verified boot and attestation features to verify that the hardware,\n"
"                        firmware and operating system are genuine along with providing other\n"
"                        useful data from the hardware and operating system."
msgstr ""

#: static/install/cli.html:440 static/install/web.html:353
msgid ""
"Since the purpose of Auditor is to obtain information about the device\n"
"                        without trusting it to be honest, results aren't shown on the device being\n"
"                        verified. You need a 2nd Android device running Auditor for local QR code\n"
"                        based verification. You can also use our optional device integrity\n"
"                        monitoring service for automatic scheduled verifications with support for\n"
"                        email alerts."
msgstr ""

#: static/install/cli.html:446 static/install/web.html:359
msgid "Auditor tutorial"
msgstr ""

#: static/install/cli.html:446 static/install/web.html:359
msgid ""
"\n"
"                        for a guide."
msgstr ""

#: static/install/cli.html:448 static/install/web.html:361
msgid ""
"Auditor is primarily based on a pairing model where it generates a\n"
"                        hardware backed signing key and hardware backed attestation signing key\n"
"                        and pins them as part of the initial verification. The first verification\n"
"                        is bootstrapped based on chaining trust to one of the Android attestation\n"
"                        roots. After the first verification, it provides a highly secure system\n"
"                        for obtaining information about the device going forward. An attacker\n"
"                        could bypass the initial verification with a leaked attestation key or by\n"
"                        proxying to another device with the device model, OS and patch level that\n"
"                        the user is expecting. Proxying to another device will be addressed in the\n"
"                        future with optional support for the hardware serial number attestation\n"
"                        feature."
msgstr ""

